1. The terminal is an app that lets users communicate with the operating system using a command line. As users enter different commands, the computer will perform the tasks. 

2. Git is a decentralized/distributed version control system whereas GitHub is hosting service that allows you to manage your Git repositories. 

3. Steps to fork a GitHub repository:
	- Navigate to the repository on GitHub
	- On the top right corner of the page, click the "Fork" button
	- You can name the repository and add description
	- Click create fork 
	
	You can then make edits and send pull request to original owner. 